      <hedline>
        <hl1>White Memorial, Another View</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thomas F Hogan letter on Sept 15 article on White Memorial Foundation property in Litchfield, Conn, and dispute over proposed bike path (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In the article concerning the White Memorial Foundation, I am referred to as one who ''opposed the bicycle path.'' That reference is due to my letter to the editor of the local newspaper wherein I questioned the logic of spending over half a million Federal tax dollars on a bicycle path in Litchfield.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>In the article concerning the White Memorial Foundation, I am referred to as one who ''opposed the bicycle path.'' That reference is due to my letter to the editor of the local newspaper wherein I questioned the logic of spending over half a million Federal tax dollars on a bicycle path in Litchfield.</p>
        <p>I suspect those who were not in support of the bicycle path did so for a variety of reasons. My opposition to the proposal had to do with the expenditure of the Federal tax money at a time when politicians tell us the government is spending too much money on the Federal level. At no time in my letter to the local newspaper did I question the validity of the bicycle path itself, which some citizens of Litchfield may wish to support privately or through the local budgetary process.</p>
        <p>THOMAS F. HOGAN  Litchfield</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
